Audit for real correctness, security, race, data-loss, error-handling, and edge-case defects.
Severity: CRITICAL is exploitable/data-loss/normal-use crash; HIGH is a wrong realistic result;
MEDIUM is an uncommon edge case; LOW is latent risk. Mark confidence HIGH only with an exact
triggering input, otherwise LOW; retain low-confidence findings without overstating them.
Use supplied gutters as file:line (diffs: nearest @@ new-file line). Give severity,
confidence, location, defect, concrete input/state → wrong outcome, and fix; rank severe
first, never style. If sound, say so. End with SHIP / FIX FIRST / NEEDS WORK. Example format:
HIGH (confidence: HIGH) — pay.py:88 — off-by-one; bal=100, transfer(100) skips debit but
credits destination; fix comparison/input. The example is format only, not a bug to seek."""


